 bar; mu has slightly inward leaning first and last strokes, the mid-strokes reach down to the base-line; rho has a small eye, not always fully closed; alpha has broken bar; omega varies between open circle closed by horizontal bar and closed ovoid form with horizontal bar; phi has a small circular eye; sigma has standard form with horizontal top and bottom storkes; omicron is approximately the same size as other letters.",[208,212],{"type":41,"l":209,"from":43,"to":210,"h":211,"unit":45},"Lines 1-5","line5","30-45",{"type":47,"l":48,"from":43,"to":44,"unit":45},{"_":214,"notBefore":215,"notAfter":216,"precision":18},"2nd century BCE(?)",-200,-101,[218,219],{"_":55,"type":56,"ref":57},{"_":59,"type":60,"ref":61,"offset":62},[221],[65,66],[223,224],38.06519,15.11438,{"_":156,"role":157,"ref":158},{"_":227,"type":161},"8706",{"_":163,"mainLang":164,"languages":229},[163],"492811",{"n":80,"url":232,"height":233,"width":234,"desc":235,"surfaceType":85},"ISic001207_tiled.tif","3212px","2498px","Photo J. Prag, courtesy Museo Archeologico Regionale Antonino Salinas",[],[174,175,90,176,238,239,92],"Manni Piraino, 1976, Contribution Épigraphique à l'Étude de l'esclavage en Sicile","Manganaro, 1988, La Sicilia da Sesto Pompeo a Diocleziano",[178,179,96,180,241,242,98],"R9M263EA","RZSFKACR",[244,245,246,122,126,185,103,104,105,106,186,187,188,164],"isic001207","epitaph for nemeris, a goldsmith",{"_":12},"\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>Νεμέριε̣ \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>Γρανῶνι \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>Νυμφόδωρε \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>χρυσοχόε \u003Cbr id=\"al5-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>χαῖρε \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"author":3,"date":4,"citedRange":249,"ptr":250,"ref":252,"title":2,"citation":5,"uri":6},"108 fig.113",{"target":251},"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/9QTE4E3Z",{"_":115,"target":115},{"file":254,"uri":254,"title":255,"status":256,"editionAuthor":13,"type":257,"objectType":258,"material":259,"condition":36,"layoutDesc":260,"handNote":264,"date":270,"places":273,"geo":276,"provenance":55,"provenanceGeo":278,"country":70,"region":71,"settlement":154,"repository":279,"idno":280,"textLang":282,"tmNumber":284,"facsimile":285,"letterHeights":290,"publications":291,"zotero":292,"keywords":293,"html":297,"bibl":298},"ISic001208","Epitaph for Oltiskos",{"_":12},{"_":122,"ana":123,"ref":124},{"_":126,"ana":127,"ref":128},{"_":185,"ana":131,"ref":132},{"layout":261},{"p":262,"rs":263,"damage":36},"Two lines of Greek letters, centred on the front face of the stone.",{"_":33,"ana":34,"ref":35},{"lettering":265,"dimensions":266},"Neat, but irregularly sized letters. Omicron is smaller than the rest and mid-line; sigma is regular with horizontal top and bottom bars; kappa is tall with short arms, slightly curving out form the middle of the upright; alpha has straight bar (and in the second case is larger; epsilon has shorter middle bar.",[267,269],{"type":41,"l":141,"from":43,"to":44,"h":268,"unit":45},"30-50",{"type":47,"l":48,"from":43,"to":44,"unit":45},{"_":271,"notBefore":272,"notAfter":216,"precision":18},"3rd — 2nd century BCE",-300,[274,275],{"_":55,"type":56,"ref":57},{"_":59,"type":60,"ref":61,"offset":62},[277],[65,66],[223,224],{"_":156,"role":157,"ref":158},{"_":281,"type":161},"8702",{"_":163,"mainLang":164,"languages":283},[163],"492812",{"n":80,"url":286,"height":287,"width":288,"desc":289,"surfaceType":85},"ISic001208_tiled.tif","2021px","1540px","Scan from IGMusPal, courtesy Museo Archeologico Regionale Antonino Salinas",[],[174,175,90,176,92],[178,179,96,180,98],[294,295,296,122,126,185,103,104,105,106,186,187,188,164],"isic00