ines of Greek letters, apparently centred on the face of the plinth; the second line sits directly above the lower moulding",{"_":33,"ana":34,"ref":35},{"lettering":548,"dimensions":549},"Simple, widely spaced letters. Omega is wide and open, with horizontal tails; rho has a large, closed eye; omicron is small and mid-line; nu is regular and with both verticals full length",[550,551],{"type":41,"l":141,"from":43,"to":44,"h":366,"unit":45},{"type":47,"l":48,"from":43,"to":44,"unit":45},{"_":553,"notBefore":422,"notAfter":466,"evidence":372,"precision":18},"The tomb has not been excavated fully, but the cemetery went out of use around the end of the 3rd century BCE or early 2nd century, offering a terminus ante quem",[555,557],{"_":55,"type":56,"ref":57,"corresp":556},"#findspot",{"_":59,"type":60,"ref":61,"offset":62},[559],[65,66],[223,224],{"_":562,"role":563,"ref":564},"Necropoli di Abakainon","site","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/186",{"type":161},{"_":163,"mainLang":164,"languages":567},[163],{"n":80,"url":569,"height":169,"width":170,"desc":171,"surfaceType":85},"ISic004417_tiled.tif",[],[91,92,391],[97,98,394],[574,575,576,122,539,185,103,104,105,106,104,577,188,164],"isic004417","epitaph for [-?-], child of gerontios",{"_":120},"necropoli di abakainon","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ω\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">.\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[Γ]ε̣ρόντιου \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"author":3,"date":4,"citedRange":402,"ptr":580,"ref":581,"title":2,"citation":5,"uri":6},{"target":113},{"_":115,"target":115},{"file":583,"uri":583,"title":535,"status":584,"editionAuthor":13,"type":585,"